All Implemented Interfaces:

Direct Known Subclasses:
BulletTrailRemnant, DungeonRoomExitDoor, Explosion, GravityEntity, HandheldFlashlight, Particle, ProceduralTerrainTile, RopeEntity, SimpleRoomBackground, TerrainOvergroundObject, WallSpray, Weapon, WeaponAmmo, WeaponBarrel, WeaponCharm
public class GameEntity extends SimpleEntity
GameEntity exists as a base class for any entity which would be rendered in a EntityManager. Class includes server-to-client interpolation, an id for entity management, and overriden destroy() method which automatically removes from the global entity manager. GameEntity has 3 utility functions: setID(String), type(EEntity), and client(boolean). These are called on instantiation via IO. EEntity defines an entity type for instantiation across multiple clients. This occurs in the IOEntities class. GameEntity does not support EEntity being passed via constructor.
Since:
1.0
